data.description:
My fellow edgy teens:

For various reasons, we here at UC Berkeley Memes for Edgy Teens have refrained from posting any explicit rules outlining what can and cannot be posted on this public forum. However, it has been brought to our attention that members in this community have felt personally targeted by recent content. In hopes to mitigate this issue, the administration and moderating team have reached the following consensus:

If posted content explicitly contains an individual’s personal information (e.g., their name, their photo, etc.) we will NOT regulate said content if the content originated in the official UC Berkeley Memes for Edgy Teen Facebook. If you post anything offensive or unintentionally comical that can be made viral on the official Facebook page, we must remind you that you willingly posted the information in a public group. However, there are clear exceptions to this standard in which we will take the appropriate action to regulate the posted content. The moderating and administrative team has agreed upon the following provisional exceptions:

• If it is brought to our attention that the individual referenced in the posted content did not willingly post the comment
• If the content is a clear and explicit* attack against a specific individual or group of individuals (there are obvious exceptions, within limitations, with public figures, groups, and our beloved administrator, Chris Tril)
• If the individual referenced in the posted content feels uncomfortable with their name being displayed. (It is the said individual’s burden to first contact the original poster, and if the original poster does not respond within 36 hours or comply with the said individual’s demands, the said individual may bring the issue to the administrative staff who will evaluate the situation and take a reasonable course of action). 

We must emphasize that these exceptions are provisional and subject to change at any given moment without prior notification. If you are unsatisfied with the aforementioned rules and exceptions, we suggest that you either leave the official UC Berkeley Memes for Edgy Teens Facebook page and/or voice your disagreements to our administrative team (please do not contact the moderating team on this issue).**

We thank you for your patience and for your cooperation. Happy holidays and best of luck on your finals.

This is an official message brought to you by the Administration and Moderating team of UCBMFET™

*We reserve the right to define the limitations of ‘clear and explicit’ 
** We will not address any statements of dissatisfaction until the end of UC Berkeley’s official semester (12/16/2016)

data.description: As a member of the UC Berkeley community and a part of one of these semester system schools this is highly offensive. Semester system schools make it their goal to give women a place to feel comfortable as well as better the community. Comparing specific school systems to characters from a movie about bullying is absurd and beyond inaccurate. Making the claim that semester system schools are cliques is demeaning the sisterhood and values they are founded on. This clearly is a stab at a community on campus that does nothing but support the rest of the nation's universities.
